Medium residual malt sweetness should be present', 'Chill haze is acceptable at low temperatures', 'Very low to medium at the brewer’s discretion 
Medium residual malt sweetness should be present', 'Medium');
INSERT INTO styles (name, category, style_id, og_min, og_max, fg_min, fg_max, ibu_min, ibu_max, ebc_min, ebc_max, abv_min, abv_max, notes, aroma, appearance, flavor, mouthfeel) VALUES ('Extra Special Bitter', 'British Origin Ale Styles', 'C7C5D020-6047-49D8-AA06-B4590EA81BDC', 1.046, 1.06, 1.01, 1.016, 30, 45, 16, 34, 3.8, 4.6, 'Low carbonation traditionally characterizes draft-cask versions, but in bottled versions, a slight increase in carbon dioxide content is acceptable. The overall impression is refreshing and thirst quenching. Fruity esters are acceptable. Diacetyl is usually absent in these beers but may be present at low levels.Entries in this subcategory exhibit hop aroma and flavor attributes typical of traditional English hop varieties.', 'Medium to medium-high 
Medium to medium-high', 'Chill haze is acceptable at low temperatures', 'Medium to medium-high 
Medium to medium-high', 'Medium');
INSERT INTO styles (name, category, style_id, og_min, og_max, fg_min, fg_max, ibu_min, ibu_max, ebc_min, ebc_max, abv_min, abv_max, notes, aroma, appearance, flavor, mouthfeel) VALUES ('Scottish-Style Light Ale', 'British Origin Ale Styles', '5CA01B57-ADF8-4B97-9059-B0BB76E10A1E', 1.03, 1.035, 1.006, 1.01, 9, 20, 12, 30, 2.2, 2.8, 'Yeast attributes such as diacetyl and sulfur are acceptable at very low levels. Bottled versions may contain higher amounts of carbon dioxide than is typical for lightly carbonated draft versions. Fruity esters, if present, are low.These beers differ significantly from Scotch Ale, especially regarding original gravity, alcohol content and malt attributes. While there are conflicting theories as to whether traditional Scottish Light Ale exhibited peat smoke character, the current marketplace offers many examples with peat smoke character present at low to medium-low levels. Peat smoke attributes may be absent or present at low to medium-low levels. Versions exhibiting higher levels of smoke character are categorized as Smoke Beer.', 'Should not be present 
Malty, caramel aroma may be present. A low to medium-low, soft and chewy caramel malt ﬂavor should be present.', 'Chill haze is acceptable at low temperatures', 'Should not be present 
Malty, caramel aroma may be present. A low to medium-low, soft and chewy caramel malt ﬂavor should be present.', 'Low');
INSERT INTO styles (name, category, style_id, og_min, og_max, fg_min, fg_max, ibu_min, ibu_max, ebc_min, ebc_max, abv_min, abv_max, notes, aroma, appearance, flavor, mouthfeel) VALUES ('Scottish-Style Heavy Ale', 'British Origin Ale Styles', 'AE2F31C1-2FB8-4EA9-9BE1-A0220624904D', 1.035, 1.04, 1.01, 1.014, 12, 20, 16, 60, 2.8, 3.2, 'Yeast attributes such as diacetyl and sulfur are acceptable at very low levels. Bottled versions may contain higher amounts of carbon dioxide than is typical for lightly carbonated draft versions. Fruity esters, if present, are low.These beers differ significantly from Scotch Ale, especially regarding original gravity, alcohol content and malt attributes. While there are conflicting theories as to whether traditional Scottish Heavy Ale exhibited peat smoke character, the current marketplace offers many examples with peat smoke character present at low to medium-low levels. Peat smoke attributes may be absent or present at low to medium-low levels. Versions exhibiting higher levels of smoke character are categorized as Smoke Beer.', 'Should not be present 
Malty, caramel aroma is present. The style exhibits a medium degree of sweet malt and caramel. The overall impression is smooth and balanced.', 'Chill haze is acceptable at low temperatures', 'Should not be present 
Malty, caramel aroma is present. The style exhibits a medium degree of sweet malt and caramel. The overall impression is smooth and balanced.', 'Medium with a soft chewy character');
INSERT INTO styles (name, category, style_id, og_min, og_max, fg_min, fg_max, ibu_min, ibu_max, ebc_min, ebc_max, abv_min, abv_max, notes, aroma, appearance, flavor, mouthfeel) VALUES ('Scottish-Style Export Ale', 'British Origin Ale Styles', '6B02611E-8700-48B9-AAD6-63751DEF0CF2', 1.04, 1.05, 1.01, 1.018, 15, 25, 18, 38, 3.2, 4.2, 'Fruity esters, if present, are low. Yeast attributes such as diacetyl and sulfur are acceptable at very low levels. Bottled versions may contain higher amounts of carbon dioxide than is typical for lightly carbonated draft versions.These beers differ significantly from Scotch Ale, especially regarding original gravity, alcohol content and malt attributes. While there are conflicting theories as to whether traditional Scottish Export Ale exhibited peat smoke character, the current marketplace offers many examples with peat smoke character present at low to medium-low levels. Peat smoke attributes may be absent or present at low to medium-low levels. Versions exhibiting higher levels of smoke character are categorized as Smoke Beer.', 'Should not be present 
Sweet malt and caramel aromas and flavors define the character of a Scottish Export', 'Chill haze is acceptable at low temperatures', 'Should not be present 
Sweet malt and caramel aromas and flavors define the character of a Scottish Export', 'Medium');
INSERT INTO styles (name, category, style_id, og_min, og_max, fg_min, fg_max, ibu_min, ibu_max, ebc_min, ebc_max, abv_min, abv_max, notes, aroma, appearance, flavor, mouthfeel) VALUES ('English-Style Summer Ale', 'British Origin Ale Styles', 'E21659A7-CC45-4F51-9BC8-A97C0DFB4729', 1.036, 1.05, 1.006, 1.012, 20, 30, 6, 12, 2.9, 4, 'Mild carbonation traditionally characterizes draft-cask versions, but in bottled versions, a slight increase in carbon dioxide content is acceptable. Fruity esters are low to medium. Diacetyl and DMS should not be present.The overall impression is refreshing and thirst quenching', 'English, American or noble-type hop aroma should be low to medium. English, American or noble-type hop ﬂavor should not be assertive and should be well balanced with malt character. 
Residual malt sweetness is low to medium. Torriﬁed or malted wheat is often used in quantities of 25 percent or less. Malt attributes such as biscuity or low levels of caramel are present.', 'Chill haze is acceptable at low temperatures', 'English, American or noble-type hop aroma should be low to medium. English, American or noble-type hop ﬂavor should not be assertive and should be well balanced with malt character. 
Residual malt sweetness is low to medium. Torriﬁed or malted wheat is often used in quantities of 25 percent or less. Malt attributes such as biscuity or low levels of caramel are present.', 'Low to medium-low');
INSERT INTO styles (name, category, style_id, og_min, og_max, fg_min, fg_max, ibu_min, ibu_max, ebc_min, ebc_max, abv_min, abv_max, notes, aroma, appearance, flavor, mouthfeel) VALUES ('Classic English-Style Pale Ale', 'British Origin Ale Styles', '079BBE37-20FA-4804-817C-8974A73645C7', 1.04, 1.056, 1.008, 1.016, 20, 40, 10, 24, 3.5, 4.2, 'Fruity esters are medium to medium-high. Diacetyl is usually absent in these beers but may be present at very low levels.', 'Medium-low to medium-high, expressed as ﬂoral, herbal, earthy, stone fruit or other attributes. While English hop character should be present, this can result from the skillful use of hops of other origin. 
Low to medium malt aroma and ﬂavor is present. Low caramel character is allowable.', 'Chill haze is acceptable at low temperatures', 'Medium-low to medium-high, expressed as ﬂoral, herbal, earthy, stone fruit or other attributes. While English hop character should be present, this can result from the skillful use of hops of other origin. 
Low to medium malt aroma and ﬂavor is present. Low caramel character is allowable.', 'Medium');
INSERT INTO styles (name, category, style_id, og_min, og_max, fg_min, fg_max, ibu_min, ibu_max, ebc_min, ebc_max, abv_min, abv_max, notes, aroma, appearance, flavor, mouthfeel) VALUES ('English-Style India Pale Ale', 'British Origin Ale Styles', '324F4CC5-D5BF-4FDD-939F-08BF5ACDCD56', 1.046, 1.064, 1.012, 1.018, 35, 63, 12, 28, 3.6, 5.6, 'Fruity esters are medium to high. Traditional interpretations are characterized by medium to medium-high alcohol content. The use of water with high mineral content results in a crisp, dry beer with a subtle and balanced character of sulfur compounds. Diacetyl can be absent or may be present at very low levels.Non-English hops may be used for bitterness or for approximating traditional English hop character. The use of water with high mineral content may result in a crisp, dry beer rather than a malt-accentuated version.', 'Medium to high, expressed as ﬂoral, herbal, earthy, stone fruit or other attributes from high hopping rates. While English hop character should be present, this can result from the skillful use of hops of other origin. 
Medium malt ﬂavor should be present', 'Chill haze is acceptable at low temperatures', 'Medium to high, expressed as ﬂoral, herbal, earthy, stone fruit or other attributes from high hopping rates. While English hop character should be present, this can result from the skillful use of hops of other origin. 
Medium malt ﬂavor should be present', 'Medium');
INSERT INTO styles (name, category, style_id, og_min, og_max, fg_min, fg_max, ibu_min, ibu_max, ebc_min, ebc_max, abv_min, abv_max, notes, aroma, appearance, flavor, mouthfeel) VALUES ('Strong Ale', 'British Origin Ale Styles', '3B628EEE-FB59-4ACD-9889-B35933895BA9', 1.06, 1.125, 1.014, 1.04, 30, 65, 16, 42, 5.5, 8.9, 'Rich, often sweet and complex fruity ester attributes can contribute to the profile of Strong Ales. Alcohol types can be varied and complex. Diacetyl is usually absent in these beers but may be present at very low levels.When using these guidelines as the basis for evaluating entries at competitions, competition organizers may choose to split this category into subcategories which reflect strong and very strong versions.', 'Not present to very low 
Medium to high malt and caramel sweetness. Very low levels of roast malt may be present.', 'Chill haze is acceptable at low temperatures', 'Not present to very low 
Medium to high malt and caramel sweetness. Very low levels of roast malt may be present.', 'Medium to full');
INSERT INTO styles (name, category, style_id, og_min, og_max, fg_min, fg_max, ibu_min, ibu_max, ebc_min, ebc_max, abv_min, abv_max, notes, aroma, appearance, flavor, mouthfeel) VALUES ('Old Ale', 'British Origin Ale Styles', 'C0C1F098-8340-4B90-99EC-88E373DB4B99', 1.058, 1.088, 1.014, 1.03, 30, 65, 24, 60, 5, 7.2, 'Fruity esters can contribute to the character of these beers. Alcohol types can be varied and complex. A distinctive quality of Old Ales is that they undergo an aging process, often for years. Aging can occur on their yeast either in bulk storage or through conditioning in the bottle. This contributes to a rich, wine-like and often sweet oxidized character. Complex estery attributes may also emerge. Diacetyl is usually absent in these beers but may be present at very low levels.Low level attributes typical of wood aging such as vanilla are acceptable. Brettanomyces and acidity reﬂect historical character; low level attributes such as horsey, goaty, leathery, phenolic, etc. and acidity may be present and balanced with other ﬂavors. Residual ﬂavors that come from liquids previously aged in a barrel, such as bourbon or sherry, should not be present.', 'Very low to medium 
Fruity esters can enhance and complement the malt aroma and ﬂavor proﬁle. Old Ales have malt and sometimes caramel sweetness.', 'Chill haze is acceptable at low temperatures', 'Very low to medium 
Fruity esters can enhance and complement the malt aroma and ﬂavor proﬁle. Old Ales have malt and sometimes caramel sweetness.', 'Medium to full');
INSERT INTO styles (name, category, style_id, og_min, og_max, fg_min, fg_max, ibu_min, ibu_max, ebc_min, ebc_max, abv_min, abv_max, notes, aroma, appearance, flavor, mouthfeel) VALUES ('English-Style Pale Mild Ale', 'British Origin Ale Styles', '71C8B5EF-100A-4CDE-B6E7-29F6B41422BD', 1.03, 1.036, 1.004, 1.008, 10, 20, 12, 18, 2.7, 3.4, 'Diacetyl is usually absent in these beers but may be present at very low levels. Fruity esters are very low to medium-low.', 'Hop aroma and ﬂavor range from very low to low 
Malt ﬂavor and aroma dominate the ﬂavor proﬁle', 'Chill haze is acceptable at low temperatures', 'Hop aroma and ﬂavor range from very low to low 
Malt ﬂavor and aroma dominate the ﬂavor proﬁle', 'Low to medium-low');
