Low to medium malt sweetness. Caramel and chocolate attributes are acceptable. Strong roast barley or strong burnt or black malt character should not be present.', 'Beer color may be too dark to perceive clarity. When clarity is perceivable, chill haze is acceptable at low temperatures.', 'Very low to medium 
Low to medium malt sweetness. Caramel and chocolate attributes are acceptable. Strong roast barley or strong burnt or black malt character should not be present.', 'Low to medium');
INSERT INTO styles (name, category, style_id, og_min, og_max, fg_min, fg_max, ibu_min, ibu_max, ebc_min, ebc_max, abv_min, abv_max, notes, aroma, appearance, flavor, mouthfeel) VALUES ('Robust Porter', 'British Origin Ale Styles', 'BFEB4190-C9D0-404C-B421-988682E07708', 1.045, 1.06, 1.008, 1.016, 25, 40, 60, 0.0, 4, 5.2, 'Fruity esters should be present and balanced with all other characters. Diacetyl should not be present.', 'Very low to medium 
Medium to medium-high. Malty sweetness, roast malt, cocoa and caramel should be in harmony with bitterness from dark malts.', 'Opaque', 'Very low to medium 
Medium to medium-high. Malty sweetness, roast malt, cocoa and caramel should be in harmony with bitterness from dark malts.', 'Medium to full');
INSERT INTO styles (name, category, style_id, og_min, og_max, fg_min, fg_max, ibu_min, ibu_max, ebc_min, ebc_max, abv_min, abv_max, notes, aroma, appearance, flavor, mouthfeel) VALUES ('Sweet Stout or Cream Stout', 'British Origin Ale Styles', 'A9A1D6BA-F9C8-4BC7-93D2-3FC9CAB6B846', 1.045, 1.056, 1.012, 1.02, 15, 25, 80, 0.0, 2.5, 5, 'Fruity esters, if present, are low. Diacetyl should not be present.', 'Should not be present 
Medium to medium-high. Malt sweetness, chocolate and caramel should contribute to the aroma and should dominate the ﬂavor proﬁle. Roast ﬂavor may be present. Low to medium-low roasted malt-derived bitterness should be present.', 'Opaque', 'Should not be present 
Medium to medium-high. Malt sweetness, chocolate and caramel should contribute to the aroma and should dominate the ﬂavor proﬁle. Roast ﬂavor may be present. Low to medium-low roasted malt-derived bitterness should be present.', 'Full-bodied. Body can be increased with the addition of milk sugar (lactose).');
INSERT INTO styles (name, category, style_id, og_min, og_max, fg_min, fg_max, ibu_min, ibu_max, ebc_min, ebc_max, abv_min, abv_max, notes, aroma, appearance, flavor, mouthfeel) VALUES ('Oatmeal Stout', 'British Origin Ale Styles', '5242D840-A979-4C4C-A4C3-55713705DAD3', 1.038, 1.056, 1.008, 1.02, 20, 40, 40, 0.0, 3, 4.8, 'Oatmeal is used in the grist, resulting in a pleasant, full ﬂavor without being grainy. Fruity esters are not present to very low. Diacetyl is usually absent in these beers but may be present at very low levels.', 'Optional, but if present should not upset the overall balance. 
Coffee, caramel, roasted malt or chocolate aromas should be prominent. Roasted malt character of caramel or chocolate should be smooth without bitterness.', 'Beer color may be too dark to perceive. When clarity is perceivable, chill haze is acceptable at low temperatures.', 'Optional, but if present should not upset the overall balance. 
Coffee, caramel, roasted malt or chocolate aromas should be prominent. Roasted malt character of caramel or chocolate should be smooth without bitterness.', 'Full');
INSERT INTO styles (name, category, style_id, og_min, og_max, fg_min, fg_max, ibu_min, ibu_max, ebc_min, ebc_max, abv_min, abv_max, notes, aroma, appearance, flavor, mouthfeel) VALUES ('Scotch Ale or Wee Heavy', 'British Origin Ale Styles', 'ED8B87CD-EF5E-4F17-A36B-F435BD733C4B', 1.072, 1.085, 1.016, 1.028, 25, 35, 30, 60, 5.2, 6.7, 'Fruity esters, if present, are generally at low levels. Diacetyl is usually absent in these beers but may be present at low levels.Pleasant, low level oxidation is acceptable in Scotch Ales. Examples exhibiting more prevalent oxidation are categorized as Aged Beer. While there are conflicting theories as to whether traditional Scotch Ales exhibited peat smoke character, the current marketplace offers many examples with peat smoke character present at low to medium levels. Peat smoke attributes may be absent or present at low to medium levels. Versions exhibiting higher levels of smoke character are categorized as Smoke Beer.', 'Not present to very low 
Scotch Ales are aggressively malty with a rich and dominant sweet malt aroma and ﬂavor. A caramel character is often part of the proﬁle. Dark roasted malt ﬂavors may be present at low levels.', 'Chill haze is acceptable at low temperatures', 'Not present to very low 
Scotch Ales are aggressively malty with a rich and dominant sweet malt aroma and ﬂavor. A caramel character is often part of the proﬁle. Dark roasted malt ﬂavors may be present at low levels.', 'Full');
INSERT INTO styles (name, category, style_id, og_min, og_max, fg_min, fg_max, ibu_min, ibu_max, ebc_min, ebc_max, abv_min, abv_max, notes, aroma, appearance, flavor, mouthfeel) VALUES ('British-Style Imperial Stout', 'British Origin Ale Styles', '1539C66C-EEC9-4DDF-BA08-BDD5DF00DBD7', 1.08, 1.1, 1.02, 1.03, 45, 65, 40, 70, 5.5, 9.5, 'High alcohol content is evident. Fruity esters if present are medium to high. Diacetyl should not be present.This style was also originally called “Russian Imperial Stout.”', 'Very low to medium, with ﬂoral, citrus or herbal qualities. 
Extremely rich malty ﬂavor, often expressed as toffee or caramel, and may be accompanied by very low roasted malt astringency.', 'Opaque in darker versions. When clarity is perceivable, chill haze is acceptable at low temperatures.', 'Very low to medium, with ﬂoral, citrus or herbal qualities. 
Extremely rich malty ﬂavor, often expressed as toffee or caramel, and may be accompanied by very low roasted malt astringency.', 'Full');
INSERT INTO styles (name, category, style_id, og_min, og_max, fg_min, fg_max, ibu_min, ibu_max, ebc_min, ebc_max, abv_min, abv_max, notes, aroma, appearance, flavor, mouthfeel) VALUES ('British-Style Barley Wine Ale', 'British Origin Ale Styles', '1354D25F-DBB3-4741-A62B-ECFCD3BFB942', 1.085, 1.12, 1.024, 1.028, 40, 65, 22, 72, 6.7, 9.6, 'Complexity of alcohols and fruity ester attributes are often high and balanced with the high alcohol content. Low levels of diacetyl are acceptable. Caramel and some oxidized character (vinous aromas and/or ﬂavors) may be considered positive attributes.', 'Hop aroma and ﬂavor are very low to medium. English type hops are often used but are not required for this style. 
Residual malty sweetness is high', 'Chill haze is acceptable at low temperatures', 'Hop aroma and ﬂavor are very low to medium. English type hops are often used but are not required for this style. 
Residual malty sweetness is high', 'Full');
INSERT INTO styles (name, category, style_id, og_min, og_max, fg_min, fg_max, ibu_min, ibu_max, ebc_min, ebc_max, abv_min, abv_max, notes, aroma, appearance, flavor, mouthfeel) VALUES ('Irish-Style Red Ale', 'Irish Origin Ale Styles', 'B113F949-72E3-4AA2-867E-8DB2341B3BC4', 1.04, 1.048, 1.01, 1.014, 20, 28, 22, 36, 3.2, 3.8, 'Low level fruity esters are acceptable. Diacetyl is usually absent in these beers but may be present at very low levels.', 'Not present to medium 
Low to medium candy-like caramel malt sweetness should be present in ﬂavor. A toasted malt character should be present and there may be a slight roast barley or roast malt presence.', 'Chill haze or yeast haze may be present at low levels', 'Not present to medium 
Low to medium candy-like caramel malt sweetness should be present in ﬂavor. A toasted malt character should be present and there may be a slight roast barley or roast malt presence.', 'Medium');
INSERT INTO styles (name, category, style_id, og_min, og_max, fg_min, fg_max, ibu_min, ibu_max, ebc_min, ebc_max, abv_min, abv_max, notes, aroma, appearance, flavor, mouthfeel) VALUES ('Classic Irish-Style Dry Stout', 'Irish Origin Ale Styles', '659FC76C-A965-483D-9C42-17827164F7D5', 1.038, 1.048, 1.008, 1.012, 30, 40, 80, 0.0, 3.2, 4.2, 'Fruity esters are low relative to malt and roasted barley as well as hop bitterness. Diacetyl is usually absent in these beers but may be present at very low levels. Slight acidity may be present but is not required.Head retention should be persistent', 'European hop character may range from not present to low in aroma and ﬂavor 
The prominence of coffee-like roasted barley and a moderate degree of roasted malt aroma and flavor deﬁnes much of the character. The hallmark dry-roasted attributes typical of Dry Stout result from the use of roasted barley. Initial malt and light caramel ﬂavors give way to a distinctive dry-roasted bitterness in the ﬁnish.', 'Opaque', 'European hop character may range from not present to low in aroma and ﬂavor 
The prominence of coffee-like roasted barley and a moderate degree of roasted malt aroma and flavor deﬁnes much of the character. The hallmark dry-roasted attributes typical of Dry Stout result from the use of roasted barley. Initial malt and light caramel ﬂavors give way to a distinctive dry-roasted bitterness in the ﬁnish.', 'Medium-light to medium');
INSERT INTO styles (name, category, style_id, og_min, og_max, fg_min, fg_max, ibu_min, ibu_max, ebc_min, ebc_max, abv_min, abv_max, notes, aroma, appearance, flavor, mouthfeel) VALUES ('Export-Style Stout', 'Irish Origin Ale Styles', 'B8A5A2A8-9328-4E5B-9229-5E6E56F5AFAB', 1.052, 1.072, 1.008, 1.02, 30, 60, 80, 0.0, 4.5, 6.4, 'Fruity esters are low. Diacetyl is usually absent in these beers but may be present at very low levels. Slight acidity is acceptable.Head retention should be persistent', 'Should not be present 
