Low to medium-low caramel malt and dark roasted malt aromas and ﬂavors are present. Astringency and burnt character of roast malt should be absent.', 'Opaque', 'Medium-high to high, with fruity, citrusy, piney, ﬂoral, herbal or other aromas derived from hops of all origins. 
Low to medium-low caramel malt and dark roasted malt aromas and ﬂavors are present. Astringency and burnt character of roast malt should be absent.', 'Medium');
INSERT INTO styles (name, category, style_id, og_min, og_max, fg_min, fg_max, ibu_min, ibu_max, ebc_min, ebc_max, abv_min, abv_max, notes, aroma, appearance, flavor, mouthfeel) VALUES ('American-Style Stout', 'North American Origin Ale Styles', '30CBA998-3C4C-4B41-A62C-F94007675FBC', 1.05, 1.075, 1.01, 1.022, 35, 60, 80, 0.0, 4.5, 6.4, 'Fruity esters are low. Diacetyl is usually absent in these beers but may be present at very low levels.Head retention should be persistent', 'Medium to high, often with citrusy and/or resiny hop qualities typical of many American hop varieties. 
Coffee-like roasted barley and roasted malt aromas are prominent. Low to medium malt sweetness with low to medium caramel, chocolate, and/or roasted coffee ﬂavor should be present, with a distinct dry-roasted bitterness in the ﬁnish. Astringency from roasted malt and roasted barley is low. Slight roasted malt acidity is acceptable.', 'Opaque', 'Medium to high, often with citrusy and/or resiny hop qualities typical of many American hop varieties. 
Coffee-like roasted barley and roasted malt aromas are prominent. Low to medium malt sweetness with low to medium caramel, chocolate, and/or roasted coffee ﬂavor should be present, with a distinct dry-roasted bitterness in the ﬁnish. Astringency from roasted malt and roasted barley is low. Slight roasted malt acidity is acceptable.', 'Medium to full');
